<p>Reviewing iteration information</p><p>Monitor the progress of the work packages in each iteration. 
  </p> 
	  
		<ul> 
		   
			  The iteration must be created. 
			  
		   
		   
			 To edit the information, you must have the right permissions. 
			  
		   
		 
	 </ul> 
	  
		<p> Monitor the overall progress of the
		  release iterations. Review which work packages are complete, which are not, and
		  which, if any, are overdue. 
		</p> 
	  
	  
		 
		   In 
			 My Products, expand the desired product. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click the desired release. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Iterations. 
		   
		  The view refreshes to show all iterations. By default, all
			 work packages not placed into an iteration are shown and are considered to be
			 unscheduled. 
		   
		 
		 
		  (Optional) Click directly on an iteration name to change the
			 details for the iteration. 
		   
		 
		 
		   Select the box around the desired iteration. 
		   
		  The detailed information for the iteration appears, as does
			 a view of the work packages within the iteration. 
		   
		 
		 
		  (Optional) Drag and drop work packages from one iteration to
			 another. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Show work package details to see the assignee,
			 the due date, and the number of planned, actual, and remaining hours. 
		   
		  Click 
			 Hide work package details to remove this
			 information from the view. 
		   
		 
	  
	  
		<p>Iteration information is shown for
		  your review. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		<table> 
		Iteration progress fields 
		 
			  
				 
				  Field 
				   
				 
				 
				  Description 
				   
				 
			  
		   
			  
				 
				  Start 
				   
				 
				 
				  Date on which the iterations
					 starts 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  End 
				   
				 
				 
				  Date on which the iteration
					 ends 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  Number of packages 
				   
				 
				 
				  Total number of work
					 packages included in the iteration 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  In progress 
				   
				 
				 
				  Number of work packages in
					 progress 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  Complete 
				   
				 
				 
				  Number of work packages
					 completed 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  Time estimate 
				   
				 
				 
				  Total number of hours
					 planned work for all work packages 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  Time spent 
				   
				 
				 
				  Total number of hours worked
					 for all work packages 
				   
				 
			  
			  
				 
				  Time remaining 
				   
				 
				 
				  Total number of hours
					 remaining work for all work packages 
				   
				 
			  
		   
		 
		 
		</table> 
	 </p>